definition.value: A long-chain alkane consisting of an unbranched chain of 44 carbon atoms.
A hydrochloride which has procainamide as the amino component.
A N-alkylpiperazine that is piperazine substituted by a methyl and a 2-aminoethyl group at the N atoms respectively.
An organic anion in which the charge resides on a sulfur atom.
Any organic sulfur anion resulting from the removal of a proton from any N-substituted dithiocarbamic acid.
A member of the class of dithiocarbamate anions resulting from the removal of the proton from the dithiocarbamic acid moiety of dimethyldithiocarbamic acid. The major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class or dithiocarbamic acids resulting from the formal addition of a molecule of carbon disulfide to each of the nitrogens of propylenediamine.
A member of the class of dithiocarbamate anions resulting from the deprotonation of both of the dithiocarbamic acid moieties of propylene 1,2-bis(dithiocarbamic acid). The major species at pH 7.3.
An L-tyrosine derivative that is L-DOPA in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the phenyl ring is replaced by a cysteinyl group. Found in the urine of patients with melanoma.
An EC 3.4.21.* (serine endopeptidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of peptidase K (EC 3.4.21.64).
An L-tyrosine derivative that is L-DOPA in which the hydrogens at positions 2 and 5 on the phenyl ring are replaced by cysteinyl groups. Found in the urine of patients with melanoma.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 1-myristoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.
A benzoate ester, formally the result of esterification of 4-aminobenzoic acid with 2-diethylaminoethanol but formed experimentally by reaction of ethyl 4-aminobenzoate with 2-diethylaminoethanol.
A phosphatidylethanolamine 32:1 zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 1-myristoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of benzothiazines that is 2H-1,4-benzothiazine-3-carboxylic acid bearing additional hydroxy and 2-amino-2-carboxyethyl substituents at positions 5 and 7 respectively.
A 2-monolysocardiolipin in which all three phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as linoleoyl.
A 2-carboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with one of the the carboxy groups of 2-carboxytetracosanoic acid.
A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of the hydroxy group of cholesterol with the carboxy group of myristic acid.
A 2-carboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with one of the the carboxy groups of 2-carboxyhexacosanoic acid.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z)-2-hydroxyoctacosatetraenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z,24Z)-2-hydroxytriacontapentaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-2-hydroxydotriacontapentaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A rac-1-monoacylglycerol comprising equal amounts of 1-octanoyl-sn-glycerol and 3-octanoyl-sn-glycerol.
An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of anticapsin; major species at pH 7.3.
A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of bacilysin; major species at pH 7.3.
A fatty acyl-AMP that results from the formal condensation of the phosphoryl group of AMP with the carboxyl group of dodecanoic (lauric) acid.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxyoctacosanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
Any mixture comprising two or more oligomycins.
A dipeptide cation that is the conjugate base of any L-arginyl-L-alpha-amino acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxytricosanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol which has a steroyl group as the acyl group at position 2.
A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with  pentadecanoic acid.
A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino terminus of dapdiamide A; major species at pH 7.3.
A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino terminus of dapdiamide B; major species at pH 7.3.
A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino terminus of dapdiamide C; major species at pH 7.3.
A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with palmitoleic acid.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxynervonic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 24 carbons and 1 double bond (position  unspecified).
A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with margaric acid.

A member of the class of pyridoquinolines that is 9-(quinolin-3-yl)benzo[h][1,6]naphthyridin-2-one bearing an additional 4-(4-propionylpiperazin-1-yl)-3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl substituent at position 1. It is a potent inhibitor of mTOR and exhibits anti-cancer properties.
A heptadecenoic acid in which the double bond is located at the 9-10 position and has Z configuration.
A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with cis-9-heptadecenoic acid.
An alpha-amino-acid anion that is the conjugate base of N(3)-fumaroyl-(S)-2,3-diaminopropanoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion that results from the transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the alpha-amino group of N(3)-fumaramoyl-(S)-2,3-diaminopropanoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydrochloride resulting from the reaction of decamethylenediguanidine with 2 mol eq. of hydrogen chloride.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxymyristic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 18 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).
A member of the class of guanidines that is decane having guanidino groups at the 1- and 10-positions.
